Package: gainr
Type: Package
Title: Flexible Gain Charts in R
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Oystein Sorensen
Maintainer: Oystein Sorensen <oystein.sorensen.1985@gmail.com>
Description: The `gainr` package produces gain charts, which are useful tools for evaluating the performance of prediction models, particularly within customer analytics. `gainr` extends the `gains` package by returning a tibble, which can be used downstream for plotting and analysis. `gainr` also lets the user decide the number of rows to return.
Imports: gains (>= 1.2), dplyr (>= 0.7.4)
Suggests: ggplot2 (>= 2.2.1)
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
